TextBody:
Hello Vipin,

Thank you for getting back to us. 

To block the youtube.com for a single user , you will have to create a new policy to apply it to that specific user. 

Once that policy is created, please go to the Denylist and under the Domain and URL, please add a new entry, add the name and in the content please add *.youtube.com 

Return to the policy and in the policy denylist, go to the domain and url submenu and add the dictionary created.

Save and update the policies on the user machine. 

Please check and let us know the outcome.

Have a nice day ahead!

Best regards,

Hello Vipin,

Thank you for getting back to us.

Regarding the WhatsApp, please use the steps from below to add the application to denylist.

Go to Denylist&Allowlist menu from the EPP UI, then click on the Application submenu and create a new entry.


Once you fill in the details, click on add to content , then generate. 

Assign the denylist to a policy, save it and apply it to the machine. 


Please let us know if you encounter any issues.

Have a nice day ahead!

To block the youtube.com for a single user , you will have to create a new policy to apply it to that specific user. 

Once that policy is created, please go to the Denylist and under the Domain and URL, please add a new entry, add the name and in the content please add *.youtube.com 

Return to the policy and in the policy denylist, go to the domain and url submenu and add the dictionary created.

Save and update the policies on the user machine. 

Please check and let us know the outcome.

Have a nice day ahead!

Best regards,

To block the youtube.com for a single user , you will have to create a new policy to apply it to that specific user.

Save and update the policies on the user machine.
